text:
The global food supply chain creates one-fourth of the total human-generated greenhouse gas emissions, with significant contributions from food loss and waste.

Using fungal fermentation, @NOFOKitchen is converting food waste into nutritious, tasty treats.
https://t.co/Z8xKKA9RG2

Worms have a nose for danger! 

Andrew Dillin (@dillinlab) and his team @UCBerkeley found that olfactory neurons can prepare the nematodes against potential pathogens through mitochondrial regulation.
https://t.co/Ua95OKGNOT

Developing better therapies against intracellular parasites is difficult in part because studying the effect these organisms have on host cells is difficult.

A new approach from @OMM_lab @GINA_GALLEGO @uwmadison and @Morgridge_Inst may alleviate this.
https://t.co/ovrgxJqbfV

Neurons in the cerebellum that control coordinated movement help regulate proper sleep in mice.
https://t.co/n7yQmFGzs2

Fungi gave us the first true antibiotics; now, mycologist Nancy Keller @UWMadisonMMI is searching for other valuable natural products that may be lurking in fungal genomes.
https://t.co/u9PpsSxIXC

Marmosets, menopause, and mind mysteries—oh my! 

Learn more about how primatologist Agnès Lacreuse (@AL_marmo) from @UMassAmherst explores the neurological mysteries of the brain: https://t.co/4oyN0N1Kz5 https://t.co/uQW8eYmDKe

Can extremophile algae turn polluted wastewater into useful products? 

Peter Lammers @ASU_AzCATI is on a mission to find out.

Learn more: https://t.co/Lcaz9oNRMd https://t.co/4di6wwSAX7

Primatologist @AL_marmo @UMassAmherst is on a mission to understand cognitive aging in women through marmoset models. 

Learn more about her work in the latest TS Digest issue: https://t.co/PZJKwijqhd https://t.co/q5lyYsYf8s

Researchers at the @Uni_WUE showed that a signaling molecule from Candida albicans impairs dendritic cells’ immune responses by altering lipid metabolism.
https://t.co/zkSV5HfiJh

#Vibrio #bacteria sense and respond to changes in cell density & nutrients. @biolluminator &co reveal a link between #QuorumSensing & metabolic regulation that confers fitness advantages in the presence of certain nutrients #PLOSBiology https://t.co/9sPFg6kqdS https://t.co/vgxHfhhbpk

Surprising input triggers a stronger response than expected input, but where's the prediction made? @D__Richter &co show that #PredictionErrors are computed at higher cortical levels; the resulting surprise signal is broadcast to earlier areas #PLOSBiology https://t.co/cPteW5f2Uv https://t.co/PvMlGhgLRc

Modeling the #hippocampus: @BlueBrainPjt presents a community-based, full-scale in silico model of the rat #hippocampal CA1 region that integrates diverse experimental data from synapse to network #PLOSBiology https://t.co/wcFjjaSxW8 https://t.co/rKjP20uezM

How do repeated #flu infections generate such a complex immune landscape? @jameshay218 @SRileyIDD &co estimate #influenza A/H3N2 lifetime infection histories for 1,130 people, yielding incidence & antibody patterns across age, location & time #PLOSBiology https://t.co/MFqqvkWmDS https://t.co/TkiotOFChu

What affects microbial communities' ability to resist invading #pathogens? This study shows that adaptive changes in resource competition between species can make #BacterialCommunities more susceptible to invasion #PLOSBiology https://t.co/MkTGuXny0F https://t.co/IPaBYrzfhs

#Bacteria in lichens. @metalichen @robdfinn @tobyspribille &co reassemble 400 #lichen metagenomes; functional annotation of bacterial, fungal & algal assembled #genomes reveals a novel dimension to microbial cross-feeding #PLOSBiology https://t.co/Q7ylPt1sh9 https://t.co/3E6QX0ZdQg

In their Perspective, @AnneOsbourn1 and colleagues @JohnInnesCentre  argue that #plants harbor a vast array of as yet undiscovered chemistry, highlighting the potential to harness this capability at unprecedented scale for drug #discovery and development.
https://t.co/XHTEqq3Qjg https://t.co/Nw33AEGavt

#Reproducibility of research: @kdcobey @dmoher &co use an international survey of >1900 biomedical researchers to reveal the perceived causes of irreproducibility, experience of #ReplicationStudies, and knowledge of funding & training #PLOSBiology https://t.co/jxKikz2BG0 https://t.co/q9ufEuC6BC

How do #apoptotic cells signal to their neighbors to stimulate proliferation? This study shows that apoptotic #ExtracellularVesicles (#EVs) carrying MIF stimulate epithelial #StemCell repopulation, guiding #macrophages to induce proliferation #PLOSBiology https://t.co/TpTGt2KGRz https://t.co/NTml39xKlL

How do DRN & WUS upregulate CLV3 transcription in #plant shoot #ApicalMeristem? text: #MicrobiologyMonday: Normally you can't see viruses with a light microscope. However, researchers developed a method to observe particles of Mimivirus, a so-called "giant virus," accumulating in amoeba cells over time using a light microscope. #JMBE: https://t.co/h7tnk636vL https://t.co/eqiIlNC5WS

text: Wastewater monitoring serves as an early detection system for outbreaks, allowing public health officials to better understand and respond to public health threats. See why wastewater surveillance is an essential tool for protecting public health: https://t.co/IF3lFgmKhb

Imagine a world where electronic devices are powered by living organisms and biodegrade after use, eliminating the problem of electronic waste. This growing area of research is known as bioelectronics, and microbes are the star of the show! https://t.co/YK6ucFBhm2

A long unresolved question in the field of toxins-antitoxins (TAs) is how toxins are activated when bound to antitoxins at nanomolar affinity. One likely mechanism for toxin activation is conformational changes in the TA complex. Learn more in @JVirology: https://t.co/GFk2DKysBc https://t.co/YBT8alPQWU
media: [{'display_url': 'pic.x.com/YBT8alPQWU', 'expanded_url': 'https://x.com/ASMicrobiology/status/1854977338078843236/photo/1', 'ext_alt_text': 'Schematic showing the conformational changes of the Escherichia coli Paris toxin/antitoxin system that protects the host from T7 phage as a backup system for restriction/modification systems (60, 61). In the absence of phage infection, activity of toxin AriB is masked by antitoxin AriA in the form of a stable (AriA)6-(AriB)3 complex (60, 61). Formation of clusters of functionally related genes in microbial genomes has long puzzled microbiologists. This @mSystemsJ study suggests that DNA replication introduces a selective force for the clustering of functionally related genes on chromosomes. https://t.co/alOaziyLOi https://t.co/XHnCn6pvpC

Grain-based diets are often used in preclinical research, but vary from batch-to-batch. Identifying a purified diet with optimal fiber composition would aid in standardization & reproducibility of studies on gut physiology/microbiota. @AppEnvMicro: https://t.co/UTft3nPSur https://t.co/qrrI8MT0cX
media: [{'display_url': 'pic.x.com/qrrI8MT0cX', 'expanded_url': 'https://x.com/ASMicrobiology/status/1853467516703494522/photo/1', 'ext_alt_text': " The type and amount of dietary fiber impact food consumption, intestinal morphometry, and adiposity. Cumulative food intake (error bars indicate SD) (A), average daily calorie intake (B), percent body weight change (C), gonadal fat weight (D), small intestine length (E), colon length (F), and cecum weight (G) are shown for mice in each dietary group. Statistical differences were determined using a one-way analysis of variance (ANOVA) with Tukey's post-hoc test. Each experimental group was compared to all other groups with different letters denoting a significant difference (P < 0.05). text:
The second round of the #polio vaccination campaign in the #Gaza Strip was completed on Tuesday, with an overall 556,774 children under the age of 10 being vaccinated with a second dose of polio vaccine.

The last phase conducted in the north achieved 88% coverage with https://t.co/3r8wKK787p

899,000 #mpox vaccine doses allocated to 9 African countries hardest hit by the disease, to ensure that the limited doses are used effectively and fairly, with the overall objective to control the outbreaks.

The doses were allocated by the Access and Allocation Mechanism for https://t.co/X2E3pDrYTw

text: ‘I'm always thankful for science and parenting because the two really helped each other in my career. Raising children & mentoring them to grow into young adults – or mentoring graduate students – requires one particular moment in time that you let go a little bit.’ – Huda Zoghbi https://t.co/pCoQdaRsR6

Happy #STEMDay!🌟  Our investigators and their labs are exploring the wonders of basic science, from immune systems to ancient organisms. It’s all about curiosity, discovery, and having fun! 🌍🔬 https://t.co/PxCD5QOU8H

HHMI Investigator @CKadoch of @DanaFarber and @harvardmed interviewed @MIT’s Richard Young about the challenges and opportunities in studying DNA transcription. Kadoch leads research into chromatin remodeling complexes: proteins which govern DNA architecture and gene expression. https://t.co/T0VfaJkahm

“I am very privileged to have a chance to take care of patients and also run a research laboratory. It's fascinating to probe into nature, but also have a direct patient impact.” –Howard Chang, HHMI Investigator at Stanford University School of Medicine. https://t.co/CKsUaTtIq0 https://t.co/VyOpEHw3T8

This image from HHMI’s Beautiful Biology captures the H5N2 flu  virus, commonly known as bird flu, which can infect multiple bird  species and, in rare cases, transfer to humans. The  purple blobs in this photo are virus particles, while the gray netting  represents a new https://t.co/GEGmYCTu36

On this #VeteransDay, learn how HHMI astrophysicist Marla Geha at @Yale is working to empower veterans to channel their skills & experience into impactful careers in STEM.

She launched a first-of-its-kind program for veterans in their undergraduate years: https://t.co/hGJqhHKG6I https://t.co/KQx7fyBJus

Cancer breaks all kinds of rules. New studies explore one of its cheats: ecDNA, stashed outside chromosomes, helps a tumor evolve to overcome threats from the immune system and from treatment. 

Read more: https://t.co/imlPwxArOc https://t.co/FHtrAXlWuQ

text:
Dr Dave Adams is unlocking the genetics behind #SkinCancer 🧬🔓 
His team's #CancerResearch on melanoma risk genes & the environment are paving the way for new treatments and prevention strategies in personalised medicine ☀️💊 
Find out more in our blog ⤵️
https://t.co/4fXqbBTsuJ

We have sequenced 50 Petabases of DNA, the equivalent to over half a million gold-standard human genomes! 🧬

This data includes information from heart cells, microorganisms, cancer, and more. Find out how it helps us understand human health, here⤵️

https://t.co/d73pMwO8ee

We are glad to see the Sudlow Review has been published, containing five recommendations to remove barriers, simplify processes, and enable safe and secure data use across the UK.  

Read this in full, here⤵️
https://t.co/taDKbTxH9g https://t.co/kWXbwyoIIN

text:
How did the Blue-Rayed Limpet get its name? 

The rays are made up of layers of mineral crystals laid down in an intricate zig-zag pattern within the shell. When light hits the layers it bounces around & produces vibrant blue colours. 

Learn more below ⤵️
https://t.co/lYMv5tpaw2 https://t.co/gwJVnsaCDo

Looking back at the #GiantsOfBotany. In 1960 agronomist & herbarium curator Dr Nancy Burbidge AM described the phytogeography (plant distribution) of Australia. text:
These are leaf sheep, and they live in the sea grazing on algae. They retain the chloroplasts in algae and  use them to photosynthesise energy from light into usable energy—food. Solar power can keeps it satiated.

Nature is amazing. Protect it.

#ActOnClimate #biodiversity https://t.co/KfXeCUwr3N

Sea otter mothers cradle their pup on their chest away from the cold water and give them almost constant attention and cuddles. 

Nature is amazing. Protect it. 

#ActOnClimate #climate #biodiversity #nature #GreenNewDeal https://t.co/UBer7x8Iqi

text:
Our planet’s most precious ecosystems are on the frontlines of the climate crisis. 🌿🏞️

Learn more about @UNESCO's #BiosphereReserves Network, and how they protect #biodiversity while supporting local communities! 

🔗https://t.co/v9QNFkpb5h https://t.co/BcGW1KeHqE

Check out this recent publication from Genomics of the Brazilian Biodiversity.
https://t.co/mo7Y4pnba0

#biodiversity #conservation #megadiverse #wildlifeconservation #Brazil https://t.co/ogaOzYpRV3

We are all #biodiversity stakeholders. 🌿🫱🏾‍🫲🏿
We need an approach that lets us act like it. 

Hear from scientists from the @CGIAR #NEXUSGainsInitiative on why (agro)biodiversity is the lifeblood of the nexus approach ➡️ https://t.co/z3PVRTEQ5t

#WEFEnexus #COP16Colombia https://t.co/iOAiHkID6C

Participation from Indigenous Peoples and Local Communities (#IPLCs) is crucial for the achievement of #KMGBF & a #sustainablefuture! #Cali 

#COP16Colombia #PeaceWithNature #ForOurPlanet #biodiversity
@UNBiodiversity

#indigenouspeoplesday https://t.co/o713DvR5Mu

Maintaining #biodiversity means: 

🐛Healthy ecosystems 
‍🌾Resilient rural livelihoods
🥕Nutritious food 

Our future of food depends on it.

Here are just 5 benefits 👇

via @FAOclimate https://t.co/W0BiFinqil

From bees to earthworms to coral reefs and rainforests, #biodiversity helps keep our agrifood systems healthy, productive and resilient.

But biodiversity for food and agriculture is declining.

It's time to take action.

👉 https://t.co/NjUFpX16FA https://t.co/wXvCCRtTXU

The latest Living Planet Report from WWF highlights a staggering 73% decline in monitored wildlife populations from 1970 to 2020. This alarming trend emphasizes the urgent need for conservation efforts to protect our planet's biodiversity. #Biodiversity https://t.co/4ZufCFejut https://t.co/JTlNJfuYz1

🌱 In Txingudi Bay, #BasqueCountry, an ambitious effort is underway to transform land back into marshes, safeguarding #biodiversity and communities from rising seas.  Read our #RegionsVoice story: https://t.co/BnUScbxNWp

With: @Gob_eus @Ihobe_Eus @HLCChampions

#Adaptation https://t.co/2NiabMa2oj

📢 Over 2 weeks, Alliance researchers joined #COP16Colombia on #biodiversity 🤝 sharing  innovation on regenerative agriculture 🌱 restoration 🌳 digital sequence information, agroecology for nutrition 🍛 gender equality, and more! 👇Highlights here! https://t.co/rniYKPwp7d

It time to ensure agriculture is integrated into #biodiversity plans from global to local level

🌱Check out our NEW publication 

'The Agri-NBSAPs Support Initiative: Supporting countries in their National Biodiversity Strategies & Action Plans' 

https://t.co/wY6cFeo0nl

#COP16 https://t.co/lnOtc4qlp0

It’s International Day for #BiosphereReserves 🌎

Today, let’s take inspiration from solutions already in action in these spaces to build truly sustainable development and protect #Biodiversity everywhere.

Time to act #ForNature!

https://t.co/Lybrhapcvg https://t.co/SegxJT0BpG

Healthy peatlands are central to the hydrology of their surroundings & mitigate the effects of both floods & droughts. World over, peatlands support a tremendous variety of flora and fauna 🌿 𓅯🐸 🦋

via @WetlandsInt https://t.co/9idLt28nyg

From a couple of weeks ago in the #PerthHills, some Blue Lady Orchids (Thelymitra crinita). These lovely #orchids have finished flowering now and have hopefully set seed #biodiversity #ozflora #ozplants #WildOz https://t.co/IXabi7XQVl

The @rp_pcp and @Cirad_AAM teams met with Katia ROESCH from @AVSFlatam and @shylockmuyengwa from @africa_resource to discuss possible areas of partnership.

#OneHealth 
#Agroecology
#biodiversity https://t.co/0Ze958uoZm

🐟 The @NRF_SAIAB roadshow with Emeritus Prof. Paul Skelton is diving into the world of freshwater fishes! Discover insights from the new Freshwater Fishes of Southern Africa book at our campus stops.

See attached banners.
#FreshwaterFishes #Biodiversity #Conservation! 🌍 https://t.co/whlkfVElTJ

Data-driven decisions are key to tackling biodiversity loss. Our latest policy brief covers highlights from the workshop on how the new RCoE-ESA Geoportal can transform conservation efforts across Africa. For more: https://t.co/HVxg5FWhSJ
#Biodiversity #Conservation #Data4Nature https://t.co/54qvigLbwv

#GreenTip 🌍 Ecosystems are essential! 🌿 They give us food, shelter, and fuel economies, but face threats from human actions and climate change. Discover key insights in the 2020 Pacific Islands Environment Report. #Biodiversity. ▶️ https://t.co/SJ7dRDqXJk https://t.co/dK9yyGXOwV

Forests harbor most species on Earth and provide valuable ecosystem goods and services to humanity.🌱🌍

⬇️ Infographic explains Why 🌲forest biodiversity is essential.

Learn more via Transition Salt Spring Society ✅
#ForNature #biodiversity https://t.co/Qj9wBv5NSK

Mangrove forests are rich #biodiversity hotspots, providing essential shelter and sustenance for countless species. 

These ecosystems play a crucial role in maintaining ecological balance. Protecting mangroves is key to preserving biodiversity.

🔗: https://t.co/JCvGjctyr9 https://t.co/ph2EtiI5zu

media: [{'display_url': 'pic.x.com/OENt38JPaB', 'expanded_url': 'https://x.com/R_Degrowth/status/1854064534127808524/photo/1', 'ext_alt_text': 'With this article, we propose an analytical and conceptual tool to illuminate connections between capital development and environmental injustices. The research examines how capital-driven industrial policies foster changes in social metabolisms and cause new socio-environmental impacts, leading to ecological distribution conflicts. It also explores why diverse actors mobilise and resist these changes. Building on Kapp’s ecological economics theory of social costs and David Harvey’s concept of accumulation by dispossession, we highlight the role of capital accumulation in environmental injustices through cost-shifting strategies, terming it “Accumulation by Contamination” (AbC). In this context, AbC refers to the process wherein capital socialises the costs of contamination, degrading the means of existence and bodies of human beings who oppose these processes of capital valorisation and engage in environmental conflicts. text:
Happy National #STEMday! Today, we celebrate our network of @CCSTFellows, who use their scientific expertise to propel California toward progress on the most challenging issues from #ClimateChange to #AI policy.

#SciPol #SciComm #STEM #STEAM https://t.co/xikzF3GXHA

Renewed MoU signed between @FIFAcom President Gianni Infantino & @ForumSEC Secretary General Baron Waqa on the margins of #COP29 in Baku, Azerbaijan. Also great to catch up with good friends from the Pacific in the #climatechange and #resilience fields. https://t.co/0OoM06tLLl

The Orontes river in #Syria has been a lifeline for millions of people, yet its facing significant problems from conflict-linked pollution, destruction of water infrastructure, depletion and #climatechange.  Today @PAXforpeace is launching a new analysis:

https://t.co/5hAUG6g6wg https://t.co/AmQCSFj6Ll

Highlights from Day 1 at COP29 

#COP29
#ClimateChange
#ClimateAction https://t.co/rVuyoL1j1Y

Climate-driven disasters threaten everyone, regardless of location or economy. 

#ClimateChange is the defining crisis of our century, demanding a defining response from our generation.

Today we are meeting in Budva at 2024 Regional Platform for #DRR to build #ResilienceForAll. https://t.co/CaZnAnOnpf
